reviews.review_text:
Masiveness........... I have not listened to many of the later shows (did see Brent's last stand at Tinley Park).  So I just went straight to the IKO IKO and you can hear the huge crowd and great PA.  The Dead at the their peak of popularity and profitability. My first show was 73 at the Metropolitan Center in Bloomington Minnesota. That was back in the day when a new LP cost 3 bucks (and some of mine got wrecked at parties being "wrenched" off the turn table in favor of some top 40 shit). Oh yeah, a lid of grass was 15 bucks back then and happy laugh your ass off shit with no edginess too.

A Dead show for me was always a cathartic experience, often tears of joy mixed with trying to keep my shit together.  I rode motorcycle to quiet a few and never died or got busted going home.
